.TH SIMPLE_SHELL "1" "April 5th, 2023" "Simple Shell Man Page"

.SH NAME
.B hsh \- Simple shell implementation of command line - A Holberton Project

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh


.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh is a command language interpreter that shall execute commands read from a command line string, the standard input, or a specified file.

.SH OVERVIEW

.B Shell is a program that reads input, interprets the line, and executes the command. Works both in interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH DIRECTIONS

.B INTERACTIVE MODE
.PP
To run hsh in interactive mode please follow the directions below:
.P
1.First compile all of the .c files in the repository by typing
.P
.RS
.B $ gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic *.c -o hsh
.P
.RE
2.Now you can enter the interactive mode by typing the following in the terminal
.RS
.B $ ./hsh
.P
.RE
3.When executed properly, a prompt "$" will appear in the terminal line waiting for a command input.

.B NON INTERACTIVE MODE
.PP
To run hsh in non-interactive mode, please follow the directions below:
.P
1.First compile all of the .c files in the repository by typing
.P
.RS
.B $ gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pendantic *.c -o hsh
.P
.RE
2.Now you can enter the non-interactive mode by typing the following in the terminal
.RS
.B $ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

.SH BUILTINS
.RS Information about the Builtin commands for hsh.
.B exit
.B - The hsh shell process is terminated.

.B env
.B - Prints all the environmental variables.

.B ls
.B - Lists all the files in the currently working directory.

.B cd
.B - Change directory

.SH OPTIONS
There are currently no options.

.SH SEE ALSO
.RE
.B Command Search and Execution
.RE
sh(1), cd(1p), echo(1p), exit(1p)

.RE
.B System Interfaces volume
.RE
exit(3p), fork(3p), open(3p), exec(1p)


.SH EXIT STATUS
.B 0 - Everything was executed properly
.PP
.B 1 - Error

.SH OUTPUT FILES
.RE
.B None.

.SH BUGS
No known bugs at the moment. Please contact if any unknown bugs are present

